Marches will check the following memories
	1. SRAM    address range specified by sram_array. (cacheable, in 0x40000000 to 0x400FFFFF)
	2. DPRAM0  address range 0x50000000  to 0x50007FFC  (4KB) // non-cacheable
	3. DPRAM1  address range 0x60000000  to 0x60007FFC  (4KB) // non-cacheable
	4. GNSS    address range 0x70000000  to 0x70100000  (1MB) // non-cacheable
	5. MIL-1553-0 address range 0x80000D00 to 0x80000DFF      // non-cacheable.
	6. MIL-1553-1 address range 0x80000C00 to 0x80000CFF      // non-cacheable.



Cacheable RAM range        0x40000000 to 0x4000FFFF
Non-cacheable RAM range    0x50000000 to 0x7FFFFFFF
MMIO 			   0x80000000 to 0x8000FFFF
	


